                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Last night I had the oddest thing happen to me.  
<br />

<br />
I logged on to finish up my current AA before bed and decided Tactics pit would be quickest.  I love my frenzied initiates.   There was a dark elf who just seemed to not resist me at all and stayed charm for full duration.  He hit for 608 and was just absolutely devine.  Well, I used him initially to kill roughly 6-7 mobs in about a 5 min time frame.  A war wraith had rooted me and he was finally down to about a 1/4 of a bub of health.  So I gated out so he could regen and I could find him again and use him again.  I zoned back into Tactics, ran back to the pit and located my newest best friend.  He was standing all alone by the wall.  Since he was still hasted and tash'd from the previous charm, I just proceeded to charm him.  
<br />

<br />
Now this is where it gets wierd.  The very instant charm landing on my Frenzied Initiate this time, for some reason, the entire pit decided to charge me.  I'm not indicating mobs standing near my charmed pet at the time of beign charmed.  I'm talking mobs halfway across the pit aggro'ing and bringing with them any and all mobs they ran across.  Not more then 3 secs after charming the frenzied I had roughly 15 mobs rushing me.  I quickly clicked the exit portal.  Commented on guild ( and got laughed at consequently ) and decided I had just run across some bad luck.
<br />

<br />
I rezone, I refind my Dark Elf Frenzied, again by the wall, this time there isnt even a mob in sight . .they were all by the portal, still looking for me.  So I Charm him, and as I turn in the direction of where the mobs are, I see it again.  A rampaging swarm of pit mobs, thirsty for my blood for enslaving their brethren as my pet.  Their hatred fueling that of the others around them.  There's 2-3 War Wraiths casting, a few oracles of zek casting, and the exit portal on the other side of the pit.  I quickly send in my pet and run like a crazed gnome outta there cursing the day the pit mobs decided to be so protective.
<br />

<br />
My question is . .WTH???  LoL this was the most odd aggro I have EVER seen involving charm in a zone.  It wasnt as though I ran over mobs, or was close to anything.  I've exp'd in Tactics for some time now and pretty much know how much room I have to mobs before aggro'ing, yet this was just stupid.  The very second charm hit, the pit mobs rushed me, and this was after zoning twice that this happened. . . Oddities</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=927934" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://members.cox.net/gnomercy/Giordiino1.jpg" border="0" /></a>   
<br />

<br />
