                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This happens whenever your charmed pet is fighting a mob and somehow stops fighting it, ie you gate, mez AND memblur the mob or die. NPCs on hate/agro lists never seem to wipe no matter what zone your in and no matter what you do until your ex pet is dead. I have had this happen to me in PoFire many times and have tested this theroy.
<br />
What happens is the orginal mob that you were fighting returns to their normal non agro script, either roam or return to its spawn location. If they roam they will assist the hate/agro of the ex pet to every mob they come close too but they will not directly agro the old pet until you charm it again, that hate/agro now becomes yours and every mob that has been passed hate/agro will automatically bee line to you and your pet, if you let the pet roam enough you can agro a TON of mobs. You can also use this to your advantage if you wish to test yourself to see how really good you are at crowd control. I would suggest bringing a cleric to keep your pet healed so the only limiting factors are how long you let your old pet roam before you recharm it and how much mana you have. This can be loads of fun  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=690499" target="_blank" class="postlink">Luminious Enlightenedspirit</a>
<br />
&lt;Last Hope&gt;
<br />
65 Coercer of E''ci</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
