                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings,
<br />

<br />
   Actually this problem has been around for a long time.  I first encountered it back in 2000 during the Halloween scripts in WC and have since encountered it in various charm activities with the most recent wiping a group, not once but twice in LDON.
<br />

<br />
   From what I understand, when you have your charmed pet attack a mob, it gains agro just like a normal, non-taunting pet does, and when charm breaks, your ex-pet becomes immune to friendly fire, just as your group mates are immune to your WoM spell.  In this case though, the ex-pet is still on the mobs hate list, so when you recharm it, the hate list gets bugged in such a way that you are suddenly at the top of the list.
<br />

<br />
It is important to note that the mobs will come after you instead of your newly charmed pet.  I should also point out that if you kill your ex pet in some way, it wil clear the list for all the mobs that had been in that chain of agro.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Elder Kaatt</a>, Sixty-Five Year Old Khati Sha Feral Lord of Xev.<ul><li>BST65.281/Xv h++ 4(3.8)khp 4.1km ft5 r10 !G&gt;++++ e++ o T++ L++ H- f+ g b !t D+ X@</ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</a>, Coercion Technician of the Sixty-Fifth Tier of Xev.<ul><li>ENC65.19/Xv h-- 1.6(1.9)khp 3.7km ft1 r3 !G&gt;++++ e+&gt;++++ o T++ L-- H- f+ g b(@) c+&gt;++++ t-&gt;! D+ X@</ul></ul></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
