                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Like others have said, this is nothing new. 
<br />

<br />
What happens is your Charmed pet gets on Mob_01's Aggro list. Then for whatever reason you gate/die/zone while your former pet was still charmed. Now although Mob_01 can't kill your ex pet anymore, it still is passing the aggro list as it wanders. So you decide to recharm that nice pet since it was already debuffed/mage packaged/whatever. 
<br />

<br />
As soon as you do all the mobs that received aggro transfer from Mob_01 realize, hey, we can kill that now... will rush you... across the zone... and try to kill you instead of your pet. 
<br />

<br />
My best experiences with this have been a year or two ago when I was charming in Maiden's Eye. If that zone wasn't bad enough it was even more exciting when 10 + mobs began to warp to me one at a time... new meaning to autopull. Another incident was in a LDON.
<br />

<br />
Easy solution is to make sure you finish off whatever you are killing or don't recharm the same mob [not always an option].
<br />

<br />
On a side note... it appears they fixed the bug that previously charmed mobs will see invis... I haven't seen that happen for a long while now!</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=432133" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.exodusfuryguild.com/images/sigs/silvsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
